  "result": "A debouncer delays running the search until the user pauses typing (say, 300ms of no new keystrokes), so you fire one request instead of one per keystroke.\n\nWhy it matters:\n- **Fewer requests** — typing \"laptop\" sends 1 query instead of 6, cutting API load and cost.\n- **Avoids race conditions** — later keystrokes' responses can arrive before earlier ones, flashing stale results.\n- **Smoother UI** — no rapid re-renders or loading flicker on every character.\n\nThrottle is the sibling tool (fires at most every N ms); debounce is usually the right pick for search since you only care about the final query.",
